	(text_box "If you are feeding 5V to the board from an external supply (instead of the USB-C port), place a 10uF electrolytic or tantalum bulk capacitor in parallel with a 100nF ceramic capacitor right where the power enters your board. This absorbs spikes from long power wires."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
